hopobject.body: We went to university together pharmacyclub.net reviews Species of small apes, the white cheeked gibbon are native to Southeast Asia and due to habitat loss and increased poaching they have been listed as endangered. When a baby gibbon is born it has a golden tan fur that is similar to the mother's and this darkens to black in the first two years. This black spot tans again in females but in males it remains black with white cheeks.
